The article announces the departure of Phil Schiliro, Assistant to the President and Special Advisor. Schiliro served as Assistant to the President and Director of Legislative Affairs from 2008 to 2011, overseeing the passage of important legislation such as the Recovery Act, the Affordable Care Act, Wall Street reform, and New START, as well as the confirmations of two Supreme Court justices. Since then, he has continued to serve as Special Advisor to the President. President Obama and White House Chief of Staff Bill Daley praise Schiliro for his leadership, counsel, and contributions to the American people.